== Access == From {{ill|Asahikawa City|ja|旭川市街|qq=draft}}, take a bus to {{ill|Asahidake Onsen|ja|旭岳温泉|qq=draft}} (approximately 1 hour 10 minutes). Then, board a ropeway and disembark at Sugami-no-ike, followed by about 2 hours of hiking. This route passes through a plateau known as Susuge-daira, offering views of the majestic {{ill|Asahidake|ja|旭岳|qq=draft}} to the right, and traverses a flower field where {{ill|Chinguruma|ja|チングルマ|qq=draft}} bloom. Alternatively, one may descend westward from the Nakadake branch along the route from {{ill|Mamiya-dake|ja|間宮岳|qq=draft}} to Nakadake.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Hokkaido no Yama|author=Kenji Itō|publisher=Yama to Keikoku-sha|date=2017}}</ref>
